description.plain:
We Got London on Da Track!

London Tyler Holmes (b. March 27, 1991), known professionally as London on da Track, is an American hip-hop producer and former rapper from Atlanta, Georgia. Holmes' foray into the world of rap and hip-hop began at the age of 16 when he joined a rap crew called Dem Guyz and developed his writing and composition skills by playing piano at his local church. Creating his own beats, he began putting together tracks for other rappers on the scene, including “Pieon“ by rap group Rich Kidz.

2011 saw the release of his first song with Young Thug, entitled “Curtains“, the first of many collaborations with the fellow Atlantan artist. London’s prolific output of material continued throughout 2012 and 2013, as he worked with the likes of Waka Flocka Flame, Gucci Mane, and Rich Homie Quan before signing a deal with Cash Money Records.

In 2014, three of his songs with Young Thug (“Lifestyle,” “Hookah,” and “About The Money”) charted on the Billboard Hot 100 at the same time. He swiftly went on to earn production and writing credits on releases from prominent artists such as Lil Wayne, 50 Cent, and Drake.

2017 saw London on Da Track put together his own label, L.I.V. (an abbreviation of “Living In Volumes”), while beginning to work on his debut release as a solo artist, Who Would’ve Known.

In 2019 Holmes released the high-energy single “Throw Fits,“ featuring G-Eazy, Young Miami of City Girls, and Juvenile.

Some of London’s most popular collaborations are with artists such as  Young Thug, Drake, T.I., 21 Savage, Nicki Minaj, Migos, Rich Kidz, Kodak Black, Lil Wayne, Gucci Mane and many, many more.

description.plain:
London On Da Track is back with the second single for his upcoming album Who Would’ve Known, recruiting his long time partner in crime Young Thug, Jeremih (who is no stranger to the melodic beats of London), YG and Ty Dolla $ign for “Whatever You On.” London collaboratively produced this track with Scott Storch and Boogie Robinson.

Storch has spent a lot time together in the studio with London, even teaming up to deliver one of the highlights of Young Thug’s summer album Beautiful Thugger Girls in “Daddy’s Birthday”

A video was released simultaneously with the single.

description.plain:
“Fuck Love“ is a highly anticipated A Boogie track which first leaked in September 2019, alongside multiple leaked tracks.

On the track, A Boogie plays on Cupid, the god of love, and states how he doesn’t want to experience his presence. He also flexes his wealth by name-dropping expensive brands of clothing and shoes.

A Boogie took it to Twitter on June 18th to reply to fans about the track:
https://twitter.com/ArtistHBTL/status/1273438242881318912
